## Executive Summary

AirDropper is a gas-optimized Merkle airdrop protocol designed to distribute 100 USDC to four addresses on zkSync Era, verified using Merkle proof inclusion. The codebase is intentionally minimal (62 nSLOC across one contract and one deployment script).

The audit identified **4 High severity vulnerabilities**, **1 Low severity vulnerability**, and **1 Informational finding**. All four High-severity findings were confirmed by the contest judges.

The most critical finding is a complete absence of claim-replay protection in `MerkleAirdrop.sol`, which allows any valid proof to be used unlimited times to drain all deposited tokens. Three additional High-severity issues exist exclusively in `Deploy.s.sol`: a hardcoded USDC address typo that prevents any claim from succeeding, a Merkle root built with wrong decimal precision, and the use of Ethereum L1 addresses in a zkSync-targeted deployment that breaks Account Abstraction wallet holders.

**No funds are safe in the current deployment configuration.**

