### [L-01] ETH Claim Fee Is Economically Impractical for the Owner to Recover

**Affected Files**: `src/MerkleAirdrop.sol`

#### Description

`FEE = 1e9` (1 gwei) is a `private constant` with no owner-adjustable setter. On zkSync Era with an average gas price of ~0.02 gwei, the gas cost to call `claimFees()` is approximately `30,479 gas × 0.02 gwei ≈ 609 gwei`. The owner must accumulate at least **609 successful claims** before `claimFees()` becomes net-positive — but the entire airdrop only has 4 eligible recipients, meaning the fee revenue (`4 × 1 gwei = 4 gwei`) is approximately **152× less** than the cost to withdraw it.

```solidity
// src/MerkleAirdrop.sol

uint256 private constant FEE = 1e9; // @> 1 gwei — hardcoded, no setter

function claimFees() external onlyOwner {
    (bool succ,) = payable(owner()).call{ value: address(this).balance }("");
    if (!succ) {
        revert MerkleAirdrop__TransferFailed();
    }
    // @> Owner pays ~609 gwei in gas to recover 4 gwei in fees — net loss of ~605 gwei
}
```

#### Risk

**Likelihood:**
- With only 4 eligible addresses, maximum fee revenue is 4 gwei — well below the gas break-even threshold for `claimFees()` on any network.

**Impact:**
- The fee mechanism creates a net economic loss for the owner on every withdrawal attempt; the 4 gwei in fees is effectively unrecoverable in practice.

#### Recommended Mitigation

```diff
// Option A — Remove the fee entirely (simplest):
- uint256 private constant FEE = 1e9;
- if (msg.value != FEE) { revert MerkleAirdrop__InvalidFeeAmount(); }

// Option B — Make the fee owner-adjustable:
+ uint256 private s_fee = 1e9;
+ function setFee(uint256 newFee) external onlyOwner { s_fee = newFee; }
- if (msg.value != FEE) { revert MerkleAirdrop__InvalidFeeAmount(); }
+ if (msg.value != s_fee) { revert MerkleAirdrop__InvalidFeeAmount(); }
```

